post_text:
Today, Thursday, July 2, 2020, Governor DeWine announced back to school health and safety guidelines for all school districts across Ohio. Big Walnut Local Schools is currently reviewing those guidelines.

Our school district has been planning and preparing for multiple scenarios to safely welcome students and staff back.

We will be reviewing the latest information from the governor so we can meet the requirements set forth in these guidelines. Once we know more, we will share more details. #InspireAndGuide

Happy National Library Week, Eagles!🦅📚 While our libraries are physically closed to practice social distancing, there are many amazing online resources library staff are working to provide for the community including online book clubs, virtual scavenger hunts and digital story times. #InspireAndGuide #ThankYouLibraries

post_text:
**** Special Update ****

Per Governor Mike DeWine’s announcement this afternoon, Ohio schools will continue with emergency remote learning for the remainder of the current academic year due to COVID-19.

We know there will be many questions as a result of this announcement; we are working quickly to address those, as well as identify alternative solutions for the impacts of this decision. In the meantime, we appreciate all of you for your ongoing support as we work through this together. #InspireAndGuide

post_text:
Today, we have the honor of hearing from Karen Paver from the Big Walnut transportation office. 🚌 Karen misses seeing her students daily and has some encouraging words for them!

𝐖𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐢𝐬 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐫𝐨𝐥𝐞 𝐢𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐬𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐨𝐥/𝐝𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐢𝐜𝐭 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐠𝐫𝐚𝐝𝐞 𝐢𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐬𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐨𝐥? Bus driver

𝐖𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐢𝐬 𝐬𝐨𝐦𝐞𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐡𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐥𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐧𝐞𝐝 𝐚𝐛𝐨𝐮𝐭 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐬𝐞𝐥𝐟 𝐭𝐡𝐫𝐨𝐮𝐠𝐡 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐞𝐱𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞? I’m missing my kids.

𝐖𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐚𝐝𝐯𝐢𝐜𝐞 𝐨𝐫 𝐰𝐨𝐫𝐝𝐬 𝐨𝐟 𝐰𝐢𝐬𝐝𝐨𝐦 𝐝𝐨 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐡𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐬𝐭𝐮𝐝𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬 𝐚𝐬 𝐰𝐞 𝐟𝐚𝐜𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐞𝐱𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞 𝐭𝐨𝐠𝐞𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫? You can do this! You are stronger than you think! 💪

𝐈 𝐥𝐨𝐯𝐞 𝐁𝐢𝐠 𝐖𝐚𝐥𝐧𝐮𝐭 𝐋𝐨𝐜𝐚𝐥 𝐒𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐨𝐥𝐬 𝐛𝐞𝐜𝐚𝐮𝐬𝐞… together we can make a difference! 🦅

Thank you, Karen! We know the students miss you as much as you miss them!😊 #BWEaglesInspire #InspireAndGuide
text:
Today, we have the honor of hearing from Karen Paver from the Big Walnut transportation office. 🚌 Karen misses seeing her students daily and has some encouraging words for them!

𝐖𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐢𝐬 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐫𝐨𝐥𝐞 𝐢𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐬𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐨𝐥/𝐝𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐢𝐜𝐭 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐠𝐫𝐚𝐝𝐞 𝐢𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐬𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐨𝐥? Bus driver

𝐖𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐢𝐬 𝐬𝐨𝐦𝐞𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐡𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐥𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐧𝐞𝐝 𝐚𝐛𝐨𝐮𝐭 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐬𝐞𝐥𝐟 𝐭𝐡𝐫𝐨𝐮𝐠𝐡 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐞𝐱𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞? I’m missing my kids.

𝐖𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐚𝐝𝐯𝐢𝐜𝐞 𝐨𝐫 𝐰𝐨𝐫𝐝𝐬 𝐨𝐟 𝐰𝐢𝐬𝐝𝐨𝐦 𝐝𝐨 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐡𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐬𝐭𝐮𝐝𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬 𝐚𝐬 𝐰𝐞 𝐟𝐚𝐜𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐞𝐱𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞 𝐭𝐨𝐠𝐞𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫? You can do this! You are stronger than you think! 💪

𝐈 𝐥𝐨𝐯𝐞 𝐁𝐢𝐠 𝐖𝐚𝐥𝐧𝐮𝐭 𝐋𝐨𝐜𝐚𝐥 𝐒𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐨𝐥𝐬 𝐛𝐞𝐜𝐚𝐮𝐬𝐞… together we can make a difference! 🦅

Thank you, Karen! We know the students miss you as much as you miss them!😊 #BWEaglesInspire #InspireAndGuide

post_text:
Today, we have the opportunity to see and hear from Susan Stein on how she’s helping her students during the stay-at-home order. Just like our students, our staff members are learning a lot about themselves during this time of remote learning!🦅

𝐖𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐢𝐬 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐫𝐨𝐥𝐞 𝐢𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐬𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐨𝐥/𝐝𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐢𝐜𝐭 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐠𝐫𝐚𝐝𝐞 𝐢𝐧 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐬𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐨𝐥? Reading and math tutor at Harrison Street Elementary 📚🔢

𝐓𝐞𝐥𝐥 𝐮𝐬 𝐡𝐨𝐰 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐜𝐨𝐧𝐧𝐞𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐬𝐭𝐮𝐝𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐦𝐚𝐱𝐢𝐦𝐢𝐳𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐥𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐝𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐬𝐞 𝐮𝐧𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐜𝐞𝐝𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐞𝐝 𝐭𝐢𝐦𝐞𝐬. Engaging students with Live LLI Google Lessons

𝐖𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐢𝐬 𝐬𝐨𝐦𝐞𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐡𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐥𝐞𝐚𝐫𝐧𝐞𝐝 𝐚𝐛𝐨𝐮𝐭 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐬𝐞𝐥𝐟 𝐭𝐡𝐫𝐨𝐮𝐠𝐡 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐞𝐱𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞? I never thought I could learn this much technology so quickly at my age! 💻👏

𝐖𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐚𝐝𝐯𝐢𝐜𝐞 𝐨𝐫 𝐰𝐨𝐫𝐝𝐬 𝐨𝐟 𝐰𝐢𝐬𝐝𝐨𝐦 𝐝𝐨 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐡𝐚𝐯𝐞 𝐟𝐨𝐫 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐬𝐭𝐮𝐝𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬 𝐚𝐬 𝐰𝐞 𝐟𝐚𝐜𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐞𝐱𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞 𝐭𝐨𝐠𝐞𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫? Mrs. Stein is learning just like you are! We will get through this!

𝐈 𝐥𝐨𝐯𝐞 𝐁𝐢𝐠 𝐖𝐚𝐥𝐧𝐮𝐭 𝐋𝐨𝐜𝐚𝐥 𝐒𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐨𝐥𝐬 𝐛𝐞𝐜𝐚𝐮𝐬𝐞… each child is taught to reach their maximum potential of learning with compassion.

Thank you, Susan! #InspireAndGuide #BWEaglesInspire

Having trouble with technology? Most of the options in the Guides to Remote Learning are tech free! Our focus continues to be on partnering with families to provide grace and flexibility during this unprecedented time. Stay well! #InspireAndGuide #BWEaglesInspire

post_text: As you may have encountered this morning, Schoology has been intermittently shutting down. Due to many districts beginning remote learning today, the system is overloaded. To put it in perspective, last Monday the site had around 250,000 active users, and this morning, it had over 2 million. We have spoken directly with Schoology leadership and they have their entire engineering team working on the issue as we speak. We will keep you updated when the issue has been resolved. Thank you for your patience and flexibility as we all try to navigate these new obstacles together. #InspireAndGuide

The students made bird perches out of pvc pipe, handmade braided animal toys and sock warmers filled with rice! The Wildlife Center came in to talk to the students about how their donations would be used, and even brought a few friends! 🐢

Thanks to the 2nd grade students for using their Kids Inspiring Kindness grant and providing these items to the wildlife center! #InspireAndGuide

post_text:
These students and teachers are INSPIRING! Last week, Mrs. Kuzevski and Mrs. Kavalieros' 3rd grade classes at Big Walnut Elementary teamed up to send 40 "Love Boxes" to The Inn at Walnut Trail, a new nursing home in town. They also created 12 dementia fidget blankets for the memory care unit.

Students packed the boxes to include: a pair of socks, an emery board, a deck of cards, chapstick, chocolates, candies, a coloring book and a framed quote or artwork created by the student, markers/crayons and tissues. They also decorated the boxes with a lot of ❤️!

A special thanks to a grant from the Kids Inspiring Kindness Campaign, as well as parents for making this project possible! #InspireAndGuide.

post_text:
Today, we are excited to feature Heather Mahle, one of our Big Walnut High School secretaries! Keep reading to learn a little more about Heather! #InspireAndGuide

𝐍𝐚𝐦𝐞: Heather Mahle

𝐂𝐮𝐫𝐫𝐞𝐧𝐭 𝐑𝐨𝐥𝐞: Secretary at Big Walnut High School

𝐓𝐢𝐦𝐞 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐁𝐢𝐠 𝐖𝐚𝐥𝐧𝐮𝐭 𝐋𝐨𝐜𝐚𝐥 𝐒𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐨𝐥 𝐃𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐢𝐜𝐭: 7 years total (aide at GRE prior)

𝐇𝐨𝐦𝐞𝐭𝐨𝐰𝐧: Columbus, Ohio

𝐄𝐝𝐮𝐜𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧: Associate Degree/Columbus State

𝐅𝐚𝐦𝐢𝐥𝐲: Married high school sweetheart (Matt) and we have a daughter (Maddy) who is a freshman here at the high school. We are also parents to two mini schnauzers.

𝐇𝐨𝐛𝐛𝐢𝐞𝐬: Love to read, watch Netflix comedy specials, attend Maddy's volleyball games

𝐖𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐝𝐨𝐞𝐬 #𝐈𝐧𝐬𝐩𝐢𝐫𝐞𝐀𝐧𝐝𝐆𝐮𝐢𝐝𝐞 𝐦𝐞𝐚𝐧 𝐭𝐨 𝐲𝐨𝐮? Each and every interaction with a student is an experience they take with them throughout the day. I am not in the classroom setting, so when I see them here in the office, it is my intention to be a positive, caring adult in their daily lives.

Autocall Update from Superintendent Hamberg:
Hello again, Big Walnut Families. I am reaching out with an update on today’s issue. Our local law enforcement officers have informed us that they no longer need to pursue the person of concern. While there was no threat posed to any of our students, we did want to make sure that we took necessary safety precautions and kept our families informed. We appreciate the work and communication with our school resource officer and local law enforcement. Have a great evening.

post_text:
This is an autocall that we are sending to families:
Good Afternoon Big Walnut Families, this is Angie Hamberg, your superintendent. I am calling to inform you of an issue within the area. At this time, we are just taking proper safety precautions at each of our buildings, due to a person being pursued by law enforcement. There is no indication that this person poses a threat to any of our buildings, but we are keeping all students inside as a precaution. We know very few details except that the person is on foot and was in the Vans Valley Road area. For parents of half-day kindergarten or preschool students, please provide supervision for your students being dropped off or picked up today. We will provide an update when we know more information.

post_text:
Providing a safe and healthy learning environment for our students and staff is our top priority. Flu season is upon us, and we need your help! You can help us by reminding students to:

🧼Wash their hands with soap often - especially before eating.
🤧Cover their mouths when they sneeze or cough by using their arm; not their hands.
🥤Not share drinks, school lunches or snacks with classmates.

Thank you for helping us keep our schools as germ free as possible. #InspireAndGuide

post_text:
We are excited to feature Cailyn Sutliff, who is one of our kindergarten teachers at General Rosecrans Elementary (GRE)! Cailyn recently joined the kindergarten team after being a reading tutor at GRE. Keep reading to learn more about Cailyn.

“Hello! My name is Cailyn Sutliff and I am on the kindergarten team at General Rosecrans Elementary. I grew up in Granville, Ohio and now live in New Albany with my husband, Nick. We are both teachers, and love to travel and explore our national parks! I graduated from Ohio State University in December of 2018, and soon after became a reading tutor at GRE. Over the summer, I had the opportunity to join the kindergarten team and have loved every minute of it! To me, #InspireandGuide means providing my students the tools to be successful problem solvers. I want to teach my kids to ask questions and help them become lifelong learners!”

Thank you, Cailyn! #InspireAndGuide

post_text:
What an 𝑰𝑵𝑺𝑷𝑰𝑹𝑰𝑵𝑮 group of students! Our BWE Student Council completed two successful service projects during the first semester. In October, they organized an initiative called “PJ’s for Preemies” where they raised $650 for Grant Hospital NICU by encouraging students to donate $1 to wear pajamas to school for the day. This program was in honor of one of our BWE teachers, whose premature son spent the fall in the Grant NICU.

This group also organized the food drive efforts to “FILL THE BUS” in November. Along with the other four elementary schools, approximately 11,600 items were delivered to Bountiful Backpacks and Sunbury Friends Who Share. We not only filled a bus, but also a huge trailer and a few cars. We ❤️ seeing all of our Big Walnut Schools come together to help our community! #InspireAndGuide

post_text:
Our BWHS Print Services has completed some pretty awesome projects for clients! To continue growing at a rapid pace, they have a goal of raising $25,000 to purchase new equipment. Let’s check out some of our favorites projects they have completed within the community!

𝐅𝐢𝐫𝐞 𝐃𝐞𝐩𝐭. 𝐆𝐚𝐫𝐚𝐠𝐞 𝐃𝐨𝐨𝐫 𝐔𝐩𝐝𝐚𝐭𝐞- Created multiple of our large format adhesive vinyl stickers to update and modify the appearance of the front garage doors of the fire station.

𝐒𝐮𝐫𝐯𝐞 𝐋𝐨𝐠𝐨 𝐃𝐞𝐬𝐢𝐠𝐧 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐏𝐫𝐢𝐧𝐭- Designed the Surve logo and printed various works for both the interior and the exterior of their restaurant. Those designs are now displayed proudly at the Sunbury Square restaurant.

𝐎𝐭𝐭𝐞𝐫𝐛𝐞𝐢𝐧 𝐒𝐭𝐮𝐝𝐞𝐧𝐭 𝐒𝐡𝐨𝐰𝐜𝐚𝐬𝐞- Created a banner and poster for the Otterbein/ BWHS Project Based Learning Student Showcase.

See more examples of the BWHS Print Services in their project gallery: https://melissamaxson.wixsite.com/bwhsprintservice/gallery

If you are interested in helping them reach their goal, please contact BWHSPrintService@gmail.com. #InspireAndGuide

DID YOU KNOW? The BWHS Print Service team is raising funds in 2019 to help purchase new equipment. This student run services department provides students the experience of running a small business, managing finances, designing/editing art and providing customers in the community with first class work. They have become a trusted leader in the large format printing (e.g. large wall wraps, large-scale prints, and creative design) since it started in 2016. To learn more visit: https://melissamaxson.wixsite.com/bwhsprintservice #InspireAndGuide

If you are interested in helping them reach their goal, please contact BWHSPrintService@gmail.com.
